description:
It's been 20 years since the O.J. Simpson trial, so we're bound to get a bunch of "Where are they now?" stories. So which of the following is NOT true?





F. Lee Bailey stole money from a drug dealer



Marcia Clark wrote a series of mysteries



Robert Shapiro sold women's shoes



Lance Ito opened a dude ranch












function answer(x) {
 a = document.getElementById("ans");
 if (x == 1) t = "WRONG! Bailey was disbarred for transferring a drug dealer's money into his own bank account.";
 if (x == 2) t = "WRONG! Clark has written a series of (erotic?) detective thrillers.";
 if (x == 3) t = "WRONG! Robert Shapiro opened a shoe-selling website with one of the Kardashians.";
 if (x == 4) t = "CORRECT! As far as we know, Judge Ito has NOT opened a dude ranch. Check in 20 more years...";
 a.innerHTML = t;
}
